  "texts": [
    "In parallel, we assessed the relative illuminance 41 of each patch and corrected its illuminance if the relative illuminance was outside the reference range (144.4-165.3).",
    "We determined the reference range on 800 patches previously utilized to identify the reference range for blurriness.",
    "For illuminance correction, we applied automated contrast limited adaptive histogram equalization (CLAHE) 42 in combination with a modified version of a reference-free Macenko approach for stain color optimization 43.",
    "Our aim with the illuminance correction was to reduce the illuminance deviation from the reference range.",
    "Finally, we evaluated the impact of correcting for blurriness and illumination on the detection performance for spots with prostate cancer using Stanford's tissue microarray with 1129 spots."
  ],
